-- England Bowls Out Pakistan for 72 in Second Test Behind Anderson, Broad
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-08-06T13:49:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/england-bowls-out-pakistan-for-72-in-second-test-behind-anderson-broad.html

          
          
             England bowled out Pakistan for 72 on
the opening day of their second cricket Test at Edgbaston in
Birmingham.  
 James Anderson and Stuart Broad each took four wickets
after Pakistan won the toss and elected to bat. Anderson was
4-20 and Broad was 4-38, while Steven Finn was 2-10 for the
host. Umar Amin scored 23 for Pakistan.  
 England won the opener of the four-Test series by 354 runs
at Trent Bridge in Nottingham.  
          
          


  


        